Why Abbey Road fits better:
- Abbey Road is described as a meticulously sequenced, George Martin–produced album whose famed side‑B medley functions as a single, hook‑driven suite. That sequencing and suite format directly support the immersive, start‑to‑finish listening experience I value more than a collection of stand‑alone hits.
- The production details—layered yet concise textures, precise stereo imaging, punchy mid‑forward mixes, crystal‑clear mastering, preserved transients and uncompressed dynamics—match my preference for strong, polished production and punchy, energetic mixes that reward focused listening.
